Description: The rest on the flight into Egypt, the Virgin nurses the Christ Child at the left, a man fishes at the right Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Battista Angolo del Moro
Curator's comments: Bartsch notes the dependence of this composition on the work of Titian. This is a damaged first state impression before the publishers mark.
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Clayton Mordaunt Cracherode (with Philipe's oval blindstamp with the initials CMC)
Previous owner: Previous owner/ex-collection: Jonathan Blackburne (with Blackburne’s annotation on verso in pencil: "P. S. – 1765 / No. 35 – 3")
